Game Dev Diaries is a game written in the Unity Game Engine that takes inspiration
from games like [Persona 5](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Persona_5), 
[Game Dev Tycoon](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Game_Dev_Tycoon) and 
[Game Dev Story](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Game_Dev_Story). It aims to 
simulate the life of an Indie Game Developer who wants to create a 
sucessful game. All assets in the game are original, and you may look at them 
[here](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1V3ah1dkfyUgTu__PFnIRU3RVJi3OgRQP/view)

The game features a Life Simulation + Game Dev Simulation cycle. 
Similar to Persona 5, this means that the player is incentivised to complete 
life simulation tasks, like keeping up with their Friends, helping their Teachers,
and working in the Cafe to earn money, buying gifts etc. These actively help them gain experience,
money and even extra help with game development.

<img src="help_friend.png">

<img src="work_at_cafe.png">

In the Game Dev Simulation, players have to pick a suitable genres and target
demographics to ensure sucess of their games that are published. This is inspired
by Game Dev Tycoon. The beginning experience you have is not a lot, but you 
can gain insight and extra points to place into the game 

