The Life Simulation and Game Dev Simulation blend together as doing the Life
Simluation section of the game well will directly benefit your ability
to make better games (not to dissimilar from real life): 

<img src="benefits.png">

This project was part of a research for UI/UX projects on making a game that 
appeals to an audience, in which I choose simulation as most of my friends played
simulation. 

You can view the writeup and research [here](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1Bi_8RYiLCA7EHwxO0ViC99XITUwWjg2Z/view)

